thread.title: New Falcon Heavy Rocket Represents a Major Bet for SpaceX

author: Andy Pasztor
title: New Falcon Heavy Rocket Represents a Major Bet for SpaceX
text:
SpaceX’s long-delayed Falcon Heavy rocket, slated for its maiden flight on Tuesday, may be Elon Musk’s biggest contrarian bet since he founded the company more than 15 years ago.

The company spent some $1 billion to develop the new rocket, which had five years of delays and huge technical challenges related to reliably harnessing power from 27 engines. But commercial demand for such a potent heavy-lift booster has eroded significantly since its inception. The primary reason is that both national-security and corporate satellites...
